<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gage</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Department,<lb/>Office of the
                                        Secretary</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington D.
                                    C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-16"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your letter dated the 15th instant requesting a copy of the
                            manifest of the British steamship <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi>, seized
                            by the British naval authorities with American shipped goods, and have
                            to state that the collector of customs at New York has been instructed
                            by telegraph to forward such copy.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">L. J. Gage</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>